sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K861201
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We plan to place endonuclease BglII and YhjH gene downstream the xylR repressed promoter BBa_K861200 to make bacteria die without lysis and lose their adhesion when exposed to xylose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kuanwei Sheng

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K861091
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: YhjH gene with a RBS and a Terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: YhjH gene can low the concentration of c-di-GMP in bacteria. Therefore make bacteria more motile. This part is the coding region of YhjH gene with a RBS and a terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kuanwei Sheng

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K861200
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This synthetic promoter is aimed at being repressed by xylR from Bacillus subtilis and being derepressed by xylose. XylR binding seqence is overlapped with the -10 region of modified constitutive promoter. It is a part of our death device.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kuanwei Sheng

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K112121

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K861090
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: YhjH protein contain a EAL domain to catalyze c-di-GMP into GMP. c-di-GMP is a magic molecule that can activates bcsB gene, a major component of cellulose synthetase complex. Also, c-di-GMP can serve as a second messager to inhibit motility and increse biofilm formation and adhesion of bacteria. Thus, the expression of YhjH gene can make the bacteria more motile.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kuanwei Sheng
